</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,849,1162]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">
The head of the penultimate instar caterpillar (
<figureCitation box="[727,839,849,874]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="25.[151,250,1686,1708]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1252,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[151,1436,1252,1662]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURE 25. Instar 4 caterpillar of Perrotia albiplaga collected and photographed 16 Aug 1990 on? Decaryochloa diadelpha, Andasibé, Madagascar; preserved; 90 / 208. Note the shelter was full of water from a recent shower when collected." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251885/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">
Figure 
<number box="[810,839,849,874]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) is wider nearer base, indent at vertex; 
<number box="[1292,1327,849,874]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="2.6">2.6</number>
x 
<quantity box="[1358,1436,849,873]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9mm</quantity>
wide x high (n= 
<number box="[346,361,886,910]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="2.0">2</number>
); ground colour pale brown; a striking conspicuous black marking from vertex down face, widening from the vertex to about the top of the frons, then narrowing abruptly in the basal half of the frons, before widening as far as the inner stemmata just above the mouthparts; a broad pale yellow-white band outside this, the outer margin more or less straight from vertex to inner stemmata, extending posteriorly over the stemmata; a short dark line through the anterior stemmata; the posterior margin of head slightly darkened. Pronotum narrowly black on posterior margin; body dull translucent pale green, the dorsal line hardly differentiated; segments ridged or folded in posterior half; spiracles T 
<number box="[556,566,1102,1126]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="1.0">1</number>
and A 
<number box="[645,657,1102,1126]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="8.0">8</number>
conspicuous orange-brown, other spiracles orange-brown, but much less conspicuous; gonads on A 
<number box="[496,509,1137,1162]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="5.0">5</number>
yellow and sharply defined.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251885/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" targetBox="[151,1436,1252,1662]" targetPageId="25">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1435,1686,1739]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,1686,1708]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">FIGURE 25.</emphasis>
Instar 4 caterpillar of 
<taxonomicName box="[514,703,1686,1709]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Perrotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiplaga">
<emphasis box="[514,703,1686,1709]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Perrotia albiplaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected and photographed 16 Aug 1990 on? 
<taxonomicName authority="Andasibe" authorityName="Andasibe" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Decaryochloa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diadelpha">
<emphasis box="[1178,1429,1686,1708]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">Decaryochloa diadelpha</emphasis>
, Andasibé
</taxonomicName>
, Madagascar; preserved; 90/208. Note the shelter was full of water from a recent shower when collected.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1784,1953]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">
The final instar caterpillar (
<figureCitation box="[505,616,1784,1809]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="26.[151,250,652,674]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,195,628]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,195,628]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 26. Instar 5 caterpillar of Perrotia albiplaga collected and photographed 16 Aug 1990 on? Decaryochloa diadelpha, Andasibé, Madagascar; pupated 28 Aug; 90 / 208 A." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251886/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="326">
Figure 
<number box="[587,616,1784,1809]" pageId="25" pageNumber="326" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
) is similar to the penultimate instar: head 3.0 x 4.0mm wide x high; head ground colour is a darker brown; the central black marking on the face is relatively narrower, except just above the mouthparts where it is comparable; the pale yellow-white band outside this is relatively narrower and the lateral margin concave. The head and body have scattered very short, pale, erect setae, longest around mouthparts and around margin of anal plate.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251886/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" targetBox="[151,1436,195,628]" targetPageId="26">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1435,652,705]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,288,652,674]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">FIGURE 26.</emphasis>
Instar 5 caterpillar of 
<taxonomicName box="[514,703,652,674]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Perrotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albiplaga">
<emphasis box="[514,703,652,674]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">Perrotia albiplaga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected and photographed 16 Aug 1990 on? 
<taxonomicName authority="Andasibe" authorityName="Andasibe" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Decaryochloa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="diadelpha">
<emphasis box="[1178,1429,652,674]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">Decaryochloa diadelpha</emphasis>
, Andasibé
</taxonomicName>
, Madagascar; pupated 28 Aug; 90/208A.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,750,990]" box="[151,211,750,773]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis box="[151,211,750,773]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">Pupa</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,750,990]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">
The pupa (
<figureCitation box="[274,387,785,810]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1450,1472]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1045,1425]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[151,1436,1045,1425]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 27. Pupa of Perrotia albiplaga collected as final instar caterpillar 16 Aug 1990 on? Decaryochloa diadelpha, Andasibé, Madagascar; pupated 28 Aug; photographed 31 Aug; adult 15 Sep; 90 / 208 A." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/251887/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="327">
Figure 
<number box="[358,387,786,810]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
) was formed in the final leaf shelter, which is silk lined; a sparse sprinkling of white waxy powder on lining of shelter and on pupa, strongest around thorax; the cremaster is attached to the silk lining; there does not seem to have been a silk girdle. The pupa measured 
<quantity box="[868,943,858,882]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" unit="mm" value="23.0">23mm</quantity>
; proboscis sheath extends to cremaster; no frontal spike; ground colour dark brown; wings, legs and much of ventral abdomen light brown; short brown erect setae on head, dorsal thorax and abdomen; spiracles a contrasting light reddish orange-brown; true legs pale brown. Pupation lasted 
<number box="[330,358,966,990]" pageId="26" pageNumber="327" value="18.0">18</number>
days.
</paragraph>
